node.text: On Thursday, EU leaders meet to set Europe's climate ambition for the next 10 years. The science is clear: we need a 65% cut in carbon emissions by 2030 to keep global warming to 1,5 deg C. But they are looking at something less than that. Want to join us to push European leaders to show maximum climate ambition? We make it easy for you. Just hit the link in bio. video credit: @hanneskutza

node.text: Good memories! Monte rosa up and down from Alagna and back; 5 h 3 min. I asked Kilian to be on the other side of the rope then I could go exactly the pace I wanted! Good to have a strong partner 😉 🎥 Andrea Salini ❤️ Skyrunning @monterosaskymarathon

node.text:
I can still count the quality sessions on two hands, and my shape is far from tip top ( obviously!! Ylva-Li is just 3.5 months!), and I'm heavier then I have ever been non pregnant.
But wow how I treasure and are proud over my body. I will do my best to keep getting stronger in a sustainable way! 
Here I finished an uphill session 200 m climb x 5! 
@suunto #suuntorun

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Emelie Forsberg on August 11, 2021. May be an image of mountain and nature.

node.text:
It's just so much fun to run ❤️
I Can't remember last time I enjoyed it so much, and I'm so happy to feel this way again.
I still don't run a lot, still building up and some days I need to back off as I feel a little tired in the pelvis. But the balance I found at the moment is stable!
#SalomonWMN

❤️
Because @salomon got it all!
🎿⛷🥾👚
Pretty awesome for someone who loves the outdoors! 🙋🏼‍♀️
Still deep into the building up of running but so looking forward to a winter with some projects on skis!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Emelie Forsberg on August 05, 2021 tagging @thule. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text:
A nice little stretch out for the legs with the two girls ❤️ And Maui 🐕‍🦺 And Silva our cat 🐈‍⬛ followed 1 km 😂
I really love to bring them along, especially when I'm alone with them, to get some km in the legs. 
Ylva-Li is 3.5 month and now it feels ok to run slow with her. 
#bringyourlife
@thule

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Emelie Forsberg on August 04, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and nature.

node.text:
Thanks for now beautiful Jämtland mountains!
I putted on bib nr for a 12 km race and a vertical during the very cool week full of races @fjallmaraton !
3.5 months postpartum, all running is making me stronger! As long as it feels good, but so far, I have not pushed my limits to far.
4 weeks of proper training ( based on my shape ) and I'm so excited to get a bigger training block in soon.
❤️

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Emelie Forsberg on July 27, 2021. May be an image of standing, mountain, nature and tree.

node.text:
Uphill training ❤️
I used to dread the uphill training some years ago, but then decided to just start to like them. The mind is so powerful!
Some days ago I did 200 m climb x 5 and after 4 reps I almost stopped ( I had many excuses 🤪) but then did the last one anyway, and how nice it is to push the boundaries!
⏰ 
@suunto

node.text:
My advices to get back to running or start running;
1: Have fun! Stop before it gets to hard or to boring so you want more!
2: Dont think pace, distance or time.
3: Let your tiny muscles build up slowly to handle the distance without getting injured!
✅ on all!
When this is fullfilled, then start going out from your comfort zone to challenge yourself and the improvement will come.

Most important, take care of your happiness that running can bring you ❤️

node.text:
Oh these dirtroads and trails of höga kusten! Here I logged my first kilometers and I love to return home!
Here a 20 km loop is more like 300 m of climb instead of 1000 like back home in Norway 😂
#SalomonWMN

node.text:
You are what you eat?
I love veggies, greens, berries, beans, lentils, chocolate and baked yummie stuff. 
When I was a teenager I decided to stop eating meat because of environmental reasons. The animal production is a big thief of the CO2 emission.
Later I also found myself feeling more at peace by refuse to eat another living soul not only for the environmental reason. I mean why would I be a part of such cruelty that animals are just because I want to eat meat? 
I know this is a touchy subject, but this is my thoughts about it. I really believe we can thrive on a plantbased diet. Both physically and mentally. 
What are your thoughts about it?

I love the simplicity of running and that running has always been there for me. I remember runs from difficult times when it took my thoughts to brighter places.
I remember runs filled with joy and excitment and awe for that my body can transport me kind of wherever I want!
Running is one of my oldest dearest friend and I'm planning on keeping it that way ❤️
